						Elizabeth					</div>
					<p>Thanks Emma for being courageous &amp; facing up to the work/life juggling act with determination to create better options. I am not a single mum in the true sense as my &#8220;baby&#8221; is old enough to have flown the nest; however I do have responsibilities for older relatives &amp; had to leave my job because it was incompatible with issues like helping someone frail in their 80&#8217;s attend outpatients appointments. Of course, this has had a negative impact on my finances &amp; morale. So I really appreciate finding you on social media, your upbeat and caring attitude is very helpful. You are giving women who are struggling with their circumstances some hope &amp; encouragement, and that&#8217;s a wonderful gift to the community.</p>
					<time class="comment_time" datetime="2017-04-14">
